{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> καῦμα</b>, ατος, τό, <br /> (καίω) <b>burning heat</b>, especially of the sun, καύματος ἔξ after <b>sun-heat</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.865, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 415, 588, 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 39, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 417, Epinic. 1.10, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πρὶν ἂν τὸ κ. παρέλθῃ the <b>heat of the day</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 242a, compare “Ti.” 70d; ἐὰν ᾖ κ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 342b10: frequently in _plural_, ἡλίου τε καύμασιν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 350, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.104, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 5.9, etc.; [τόποι] ὑπὸ καυμάτων διαφθειρόμενοι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 11.12; καύματα καὶ χειμῶνες 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Pietate - Herkulanische Studien” 87 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, also of frost, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 3.98b, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Lex.” 2. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>fever heat</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.49 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>inflamed</b> conditions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 19, “Aph.” 7.13: _metaphorically_, of love, κ. ἀρσενικόν “Anthologia Graeca” 12.87. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in <i>plural</i>, <b>holes burnt by cautery</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 11, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 863a31. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>brand</b> on cattle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.3171.44 (Orchom. _Boeotian dialect_). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>embers</b> of sacrifices, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 12o d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>firewood,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PLond. 3.1166.6, +others (1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2738","accentedUnicode":"καῦμα","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2545","matchingForm":"καίω","stepTransliteration":"kaiō","gloss":"to kindle/burn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"燒著, 點著","_es_Gloss":"encender/quemar","_zh_Gloss":"烧着, 点着"},{"strongNumber":"G2739","matchingForm":"καυματίζω","stepTransliteration":"kaumatizō","gloss":"to scorch","_zh_tw_Gloss":"一曬","_es_Gloss":"quemar","_zh_Gloss":"一晒"}],"shortDef":"(scorching) heat","mediumDef":"(scorching) heat <br /><b>heat, scorching</b>, or <b>burning heat,</b> <ref='Rev.7.16'>Rev. 7:16;</ref> 16:9*","stepGloss":"heat","stepTransliteration":"kauma","count":2,"_es_Definition":"calor","_zh_tw_Definition":"燃燒, 熱氣 (啟 7:16, 16:9)","_zh_Definition":"燃烧, 热气 (启 7:16, 16:9)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sức nóng; hơi nóng nung đốt","_zh_tw_Gloss":"炎熱, 熱","_es_Gloss":"calor","_zh_Gloss":"炎热, 热"}]}